    <section id="intro">
        <title>Introduction</title>

        <para>
            Mango Lassi is a tool to connect desktop sessions to share their input devices.
            Once the desktop sessions are connected, you can control the desktop session of
            one computer with the mouse/keyboard of another.
        </para>

        <para>
            Mango Lassi is similar to x2x
            <footnote><para>
                    <ulink url="http://github.com/dottedmag/x2x"><citetitle>http://github.com/dottedmag/x2x</citetitle></ulink>
            </para></footnote>
            (but is usable for regular users without command line skills) or Synergy
            <footnote><para>
                    <ulink url="http://synergy2.sourceforge.net/"><citetitle>http://synergy2.sourceforge.net/</citetitle></ulink>
            </para></footnote> (but done right).
        </para>

        <para>
            As of writing this, Mango Lassi only works on systems running GTK+ on X11, along
            with Avahi and libnotify. Porting it do other systems such as Windows and/or Mac OS X
            is considered.
        </para>

